Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:10.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and of course the answers yes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:12.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and so we were not looked at the lord turin
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:13.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in fact we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:14.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,couldn't find anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.30,0:09:16.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who would assess what the baseline is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.30,0:09:19.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so what are these algorithms being compared against
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:21.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,how do you know whether an algorithm is improving
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.67,0:09:22.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the state of the art
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.70,0:09:24.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you don't know how well humans are performing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.20,0:09:26.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and so that's what we set out to do
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.97,0:09:27.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,at the very beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.93,0:09:29.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is just to ask a really simple question
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:34.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is the ai these algorithms any better than you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:34.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,in me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.77,0:09:37.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and potential people who are making these decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:39.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then we want to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.97,0:09:43.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,what is the nature of that racial bias that we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:44.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then can we fix it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.13,0:09:45.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so we're going to start by answering this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.57,0:09:47.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then we're going to get to those other questions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.73,0:09:48.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,all right I'm going to stop right here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:50.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and we'll pick it up in a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.07,0:09:51.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and start getting at this question right here
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:53.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you in a few minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:10:00.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,where we left off was that we saw that commercial
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:02.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,softer that is being used in the courts
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.93,0:10:04.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,seems to have a racial problem
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:08.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that is that these algorithms are more likely
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:09.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you are black
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.67,0:10:11.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to say that you are at high risk
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:13.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then if you are white
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:15.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and they are more likely to say that you are
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.10,0:10:16.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you are white
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.77,0:10:18.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that you are low risk when you are not
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.50,0:10:21.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so there's this dual ace symmetry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:23.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it disproportionately affects black people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:25.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by saying they're high risk
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.00,0:10:27.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and it disproportionately affects white people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.20,0:10:29.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,by saying that they are low risk
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.13,0:10:30.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,when in fact they are not
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:32.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and as I mentioned julian
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.93,0:10:34.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to start off by just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.37,0:10:35.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,asking a very basic question
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.97,0:10:38.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which is if you're going to use these algorithms
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.37,0:10:39.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,surely we should understand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:42.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,where are we the human
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:43.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and making this judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.40,0:10:44.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and then we can start getting at
