Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.77,0:28:21.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,that are themselves very tightly coupled
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.07,0:28:23.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,why why am I doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.87,0:28:24.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,well if I can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.67,0:28:26.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,drive these dots apart from each other
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.87,0:28:28.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and keep them coupled well
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.53,0:28:29.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then I can separate them
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.53,0:28:31.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can draw a line down the middle and say
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.30,0:28:34.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,red dots yellow dots one class the other class
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.90,0:28:37.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so this is the objective function for lda
